00:53:40.965 --> 00:53:43.340
KEVIN VLK: So you can talk a
little bit about your George

00:53:43.340 --> 00:53:45.599
Lopez Foundation?

00:53:45.599 --> 00:53:46.390
GEORGE LOPEZ: Yeah.

00:53:49.650 --> 00:53:53.580
You know, I was born
with kidney disease,

00:53:53.580 --> 00:53:57.295
and I didn't realize it
until it was way advanced.

00:53:57.295 --> 00:54:00.020
You know, kidney disease
is a kind of a slow thing,

00:54:00.020 --> 00:54:01.020
and it shows as fatigue.

00:54:01.020 --> 00:54:03.240
You know, a lot of people
are fatigued, and they say,

00:54:03.240 --> 00:54:04.198
you know, I'm so tired.

00:54:04.198 --> 00:54:07.570
And you think it's because
you're working hard.

00:54:07.570 --> 00:54:11.690
So when I got well,
almost 10 years ago,

00:54:11.690 --> 00:54:13.870
that I decided
that-- and I remember

00:54:13.870 --> 00:54:15.022
telling my doctor this.

00:54:15.022 --> 00:54:17.480
I said, I just want to go in,
I just want to get this done.

00:54:17.480 --> 00:54:20.130
I don't want to become a
poster boy for kidney disease.

00:54:20.130 --> 00:54:22.800
I just want to get well, and I
just want to go back to work,

00:54:22.800 --> 00:54:23.540
you know.

00:54:23.540 --> 00:54:25.970
And then when I was
laying in the hospital

00:54:25.970 --> 00:54:27.724
after I'd had it
done, maybe a day.

00:54:27.724 --> 00:54:29.390
I had it done on a
Tuesday or Wednesday.

00:54:29.390 --> 00:54:33.420
Thursday morning when I got up,
was clearer than I'd ever been,

00:54:33.420 --> 00:54:37.780
and I was healthy
for the first time.

00:54:37.780 --> 00:54:39.970
At that moment, I
decided that I could not

00:54:39.970 --> 00:54:42.790
turn my back on people who
are sick, especially kids.

00:54:42.790 --> 00:54:44.850
So I have a foundation
that raises money

00:54:44.850 --> 00:54:48.580
to send kids to camp
who are on dialysis,

00:54:48.580 --> 00:54:51.080
or are awaiting transplants,
or have had transplants,

00:54:51.080 --> 00:54:53.355
so that they get
to be like kids.

00:54:53.355 --> 00:54:56.390
You know, and go out and
fish, and play basketball,

00:54:56.390 --> 00:54:59.240
and be around kids that
are just like them.

00:54:59.240 --> 00:55:01.440
So I do that a
couple times a year.

00:55:01.440 --> 00:55:04.340
And then also, just to raise
awareness for kidney disease,

00:55:04.340 --> 00:55:07.170
but also for just
health, overall.

00:55:07.170 --> 00:55:10.590
Because the thing that
I was a victim of,

00:55:10.590 --> 00:55:15.360
was that as a culture, we don't
necessarily go to the doctor.

00:55:18.040 --> 00:55:20.754
As my grandmother would say
so perfectly, hey, Grammy,

00:55:20.754 --> 00:55:21.920
you should go to the doctor.

00:55:21.920 --> 00:55:23.961
No, porque they're going
to find something wrong.

00:55:28.860 --> 00:55:32.170
I actually heard somebody
go to the doctor,

00:55:32.170 --> 00:55:35.610
find out that he was sick, and
get mad at his wife, and said,

00:55:35.610 --> 00:55:39.520
you made me go to the
doctor and now I'm sick.

00:55:39.520 --> 00:55:42.020
I wasn't sick yesterday, and
now I gotta keep going back.

00:55:42.020 --> 00:55:43.311
That's why I didn't want to go.

00:55:43.311 --> 00:55:46.034
Because if you go once, they're
gonna make you keep going back,

00:55:46.034 --> 00:55:47.200
and that's how they get you.

00:55:47.200 --> 00:55:48.080
You keep going back.

00:55:50.660 --> 00:55:54.750
So we do need to-- I mean,
clearly, here everybody

00:55:54.750 --> 00:55:56.200
eats well.

00:55:56.200 --> 00:55:59.490
You can even eat
the flowers here.

00:55:59.490 --> 00:56:04.630
So that thing, of
eating the right things.

00:56:04.630 --> 00:56:06.710
And already, Latinos,
we eat a lot of fruit,

00:56:06.710 --> 00:56:07.780
we just put chili on it.

00:56:07.780 --> 00:56:10.170
So we have to put half chili.

00:56:10.170 --> 00:56:14.422
Low sodium [SPEAKING SPANISH].

00:56:14.422 --> 00:56:16.130
KEVIN VLK: Well, thank
you for everything

00:56:16.130 --> 00:56:17.050
you do with your foundation.

00:56:17.050 --> 00:56:18.850
GEORGE LOPEZ: Oh, it's
an honor, thank you.

00:56:18.850 --> 00:56:19.330
KEVIN VLK: It's wonderful.

